    What is the difference between a image and a picture?
    Image - Any visual object that's modified or altered by a computer or an imaginary object created using a computer. Photo or photograph - Anything taken by a camera, digital camera, or photocopier. Picture - A drawing, painting, or artwork created on a computer.30 Jun 2020

    How do I search using an image?
    Search with an image saved on your device
    1. On your Android phone or tablet, open the Google app .
    2. At the bottom, tap Discover.
    3. In the search bar, tap Google Lens .
    4. Take or upload a photo to use for your search: ...
    5. Select the area you want to use for your search: ...
    6. At the bottom, scroll to find your search results.

    How to do Google image search?
    Search with a URL
    1. On your computer, go to a web browser and access the website with the image you want to use.
    2. To copy the URL, right-click on the image and click Copy image address.
    3. Go to Google Images.
    4. Click Search by image. Paste image link.
    5. In the text box, paste the URL and click Search.
